# AI Agent Workflow

Treat project files as the source of truth, not prior chat history.

## Start Every Session

1. Read `AGENTS.md`.
2. Read `docs/ai-context.md`.
3. Read `docs/agent-library.md`.
4. Unless privacy is `private-local`, read `docs/suggested-assets.md` and follow suggested shared assets.
5. Read task-specific files as needed.

## Agent Library

- Before substantive work, query shared assets when not `private-local`.
- Never read or promote to `05_Agent-Library` for `private-local` projects.
- Write back to project docs first; promote only when useful across a second project.

## Before Changing Files

- Check Git status with `git status --short --branch`.
- If the workspace is dirty, report changes before broad edits.
- Do not delete, overwrite, move, or push without explicit user confirmation.

## Long-Running Agent Work

- Work in stages: plan, change, verify, summarize.
- After each stage, state what changed and the suggested commit message.
- Do not claim completion until evidence has been checked.

## Handoff Rules

- Write important conclusions back to project Markdown files.
- Do not rely on chat history as the only project memory.
